Second Lady Karen Pence visited Santiago, Chile, where she observed an art therapy session with children at the Teleton Foundation. She received a piece of art from one of the young patients, which she plans to hang in her office at the White House. She also participated in a roundtable discussion with art therapists and university administrators at Espacio Crea. Later, in Panama City, Panama, Mrs. Pence joined the Vice President for a visit to Cocoli Locks and participated in an art therapy roundtable discussion with practitioners and psychology students.